Package com.camerontec.util.datamodel.expression.compiler.functions

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Function
    Instances of this interface are functions supported by the expression language.
    FunctionLibrary
    Interface describing the compiler's functions library.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClasspathBasedFunctionLibrary
    Classpath-based implementation of FunctionLibrary which dynamically loads functions from the classpath at start-up.
    CompileOnlyFunctionLibrary
    Metadata-based FunctionLibrary implementation which can be used for compilation purposes only.
    FunctionMetadata
    The metadata of a function consists in: The function's name The function's description The function's signatures, each comprised of: A return type Parameter specifications.
    FunctionMetadata.Signature
    Function signature.
    FunctionMetadata.Signature.Parameter
    Function parameter metadata.
    FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType
    Function return type metadata, which can be: Fixed to a given data type (in which case this metadata has a FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType.specificationType equal to FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType.FunctionReturnTypeSpecificationType.FIXED and a non-null FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType.fixedDataType), or equal to the data type of one of the function's parameters (in which case this metadata has a FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType.specificationType equal to FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType.FunctionReturnTypeSpecificationType.SAME_AS_PARAMETER and a FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType.parameterIndex greater than or equal to zero and less than the function's number of parameters).
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    FunctionMetadata.Signature.ReturnType.FunctionReturnTypeSpecificationType
    Enumeration of the available specification types.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DuplicateFunctionDefinitionException
    Instances of this unchecked exception type are thrown when a duplicated function definition is encountered.
    FunctionDefinitionException
    Instances of this unchecked exception type are thrown when an invalid function definition is encountered when loading the functions library.
